deals.name: September deal
deals.text: Sent him estimate today.. fingers crossed!
deals.author: David S.

notes.author: David S.
notes.text:
At today’s meeting Joe outlined his needs for the next 6 months. He asked me to quote for the delivery
of 48 solar panels to Burlington. He mentioned another sp provider
so there is competition for this deal.

notes.author: David S.
notes.text: Joe just called to schedule a meeting for 03/23 to discuss his requirements for the next 6 months.

notes.author: David S.
notes.text:
Due to a shipping delay I had to call Joe today to let him know that he wouldn’t be
getting his Salem store delivery until 03/22. To apologise for the delay I’m giving
him a 10% discount on his next order.

notes.author: David S.
notes.text:
I rang Joe to confirm his order. He confirmed an order for 16 solar panels for his store in Burlington.
He amended his order for the store in Salem from 12 to 24 due to
an ’unprecedented demand’ for eco products.

contact.background:
I met Jane at the annual Eco Conference in Florida. Her company currently provides
solar panels (along with a lot of other stuff) to the State Government of
California, Nevada, Oregon, Arizona and Utah for capital building projects. Her
current supplier is crazy expensive! I've asked to be able to tender for their next order.

next_actions.text: Contact Jane to confirm she has received our deal

next_action.text: Contact Jane to confirm she has received our deal

notes.author: David S.
notes.text:
Emailed Jane for details on their sp requirements. They required 250 solar panels by April 30th.
They want all tenders in by March 31st.

notes.author: David S.
notes.text: Received email from Jane. Board are happy for us to tender for the next order. These will be know next week.

notes.author: David S.
notes.text:
I called Jane to confirm that she had received our prospectus. She mentioned how
impressed she was with our competitive pricing structures. She will be bringing this to the
board on 02/17 at the next board meeting. She promised to contact me after.

notes.author: David S.
notes.text:
Called Jane today to discuss the possibility of us doing business together.
She requires board approval before changing suppliers so requested a company prospectus.
She did sound positive though
